main event: A military aircraft observed an unidentified flying object (UFO) in flight over the Pacific Ocean on March 14, 1964.
interesting points: The UFO was observed at an elevation of 50 degrees above the horizon, traveling towards the east at a very fast speed.
The sighting was reported via a CIRVIS (Communications Instructions for Reporting Vital Intelligence Sightings) report, but the report contained insufficient data for evaluation.
The sighting was reported to multiple military and intelligence agencies, including the Department of the Air Force, the Central Intelligence Agency, and the Defense Intelligence Agency.
The location of the sighting was reported as 43-01N 171-40W, which is in the Pacific Ocean.
The report indicates that there were two observers of the UFO from the military aircraft.
witnesses: two observers from a military aircraft
photographs: yes, the report indicates that photographs were taken
